			[ Release notes ]



Previous version: 1.80n		(25/02/2005)
Current version:  1.80o		(09/03/2005)

SubVersion (CVS) revision: $Id$

TiEmu is available for 2 platforms:
Linux (GTK), Windows (GTK).

If you have a SilverLink cable (TI-GRAPH LINK USB), you will need to retrieve
a Linux/Win32/Mac OS-X driver on the Linux Programmer Group at 
<http://lpg.ticalc.org/prj_usb>.

For the other link cables, no driver is needed because it's provided.


New capabilities:
-----------------

	- program entry breakpoint feature now useable with AMS >= 2.00 
	- added Win32 file selector


Improvements:
-------------

	- handles are now displayed fine with PedRom
	- improved dbg windows behaviour: save/restore size, position and state (hide/minimized)
	- updated manpage
	- command line improved and up-to-date
	- cleaned-up configure.ac script (CygWin & MinGW)
		

Bug fixes:
----------

	- bug in ti68k_get_hw_param_block (wrong search/replace)
	- TAB char (0x09) pb in the dbg_mem window (Lionel)
	- Step Over
	- dependancy problem with tiemu&uae rule in src/Makefile.in
	- bad use of sizeof in hw_io_init
	- MinGW path with Kevin
	- -mms-bitfields issue with UAE Makefile under MinGW (Kevin)
	- out-of-range access with io_bit_tst in ports.c (Kevin)
	- contrast on TI92+


To do:
------

	- implement the HW2 Protection (HW1 protection if almost complete)
	- implement the RTC introduced with AMS 2.09

	
Notes:
------

